# Paths Semgrep should not scan. Excluding noise at the source is the cheapest
# way to cut false positives — but only for code that genuinely should not be
# assessed (generated code, vendored deps, fixtures, migrations).
#
# Semgrep already ignores common dependency/build dirs by default; these are
# project-specific additions you would tune for a real repo.

# Local virtual environment — cover common naming conventions
sastvenv/
.venv/
venv/
env/
.env/
*venv*/
*env*/

# Vendored / third-party code we don't own
vendor/
third_party/

# Generated artefacts and migrations (reviewed separately, not by app rules)
**/migrations/
*_pb2.py

# Test fixtures often contain deliberately "bad" snippets that aren't shipped
tests/fixtures/
